<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Privacy Policy – PinMyBlogs</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Oxygen,
          Ubuntu, Cantarell, "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.6;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        background-color: #f9fafb;
        color: #111827;
      }

      .container {
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 40px 20px;
        background-color: #ffffff;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 2rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
      }

      h2 {
        font-size: 1.4rem;
        margin-top: 2rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      }

      p {
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
      }

      ul {
        margin-left: 1.2rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
      }

      li {
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      }

      footer {
        margin-top: 3rem;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: #6b7280;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <h1>
        Privacy Policy for <a href="/start">pinmyblogs.com</a>
      </h1>
      <p>
        Pin-My-Blogs respects your privacy and is committed to protecting it.
        This Privacy Policy explains how the PinMyBlogs browser extension
        handles user data.
      </p>
      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        PinMyBlogs does <strong>not</strong> collect, track, or transmit personal
        information.
      </p>
      <p>
        The extension may temporarily access the following data
        <strong>only after explicit user interaction</strong>
        (such as clicking the extension icon):
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Webpage URL</li>
        <li>Webpage title</li>
        <li>User-selected content (if applicable)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This data is used solely to allow users to save or pin blog pages.</p>
      <h2>How Information Is Used</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To save and manage pinned blog content</li>
        <li>To store user preferences locally within the browser</li>
        <li>To provide core extension functionality</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        All data is stored <strong>locally on the user’s device</strong>
        using browser storage APIs.
      </p>
      <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>PinMyBlogs:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Does <strong>not</strong> sell, rent, or share user data
        </li>
        <li>
          Does <strong>not</strong> send data to external servers
        </li>
        <li>
          Does <strong>not</strong> use analytics, trackers, or third-party services
        </li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Permissions Explanation</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>activeTab / host permissions</strong>:
          Used only to access the currently active webpage after user action
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>storage</strong>:
          Used to store user preferences and pinned blog data locally
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>Permissions are limited to what is necessary for functionality.</p>
      <h2>Data Security</h2>
      <p>
        Since all data remains on the user’s device and no external transmission
        occurs, the risk of data exposure is minimal.
      </p>
      <h2>User Control</h2>
      <p>Users can:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Remove pinned data at any time</li>
        <li>Clear extension storage via browser settings</li>
        <li>Uninstall the extension to remove all stored data</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any changes will be
        reflected on this page.
      </p>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact:</p>
      <p>
        <strong>Email:</strong> pinmyblogs@gmail.com
        <br />
        <strong>Extension Name:</strong> PinMyBlogs
      </p>
      {{ template "widget/public_footer" . }}
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
